definitions.definition: Of or pertaining to the larynx .
Made by or with constriction of the larynx with only the front part of the vocal cords vibrating , giving a very low frequency and producing what is known as " creaky voice ."

main_definition: ( anatomy , relational ) Of or pertaining to the larynx .
secondary_definitions: ( phonetics , relational ) ( of a speech sound ) Made by or with constriction of the larynx with only the front part of the vocal cords vibrating , giving a very low frequency and producing what is known as " creaky voice ."
